(1, 'Managed Security Services', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:22px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Provider of Trusted Cyber Security Services</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Cyber dangers are real, persistent, and developing at a breakneck pace. Almost half of UK financial institutions had a breach in the previous year, but this figure increases to 68% for medium-sized financial institutions and 75% for big financial institutions. As cybercriminals&#39; techniques evolve, organizations of all sizes must establish a planned, coordinated, and robust approach to proactively avoid, identify, and disrupt attacks - and that is where we can assist.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">aammsecurities will guarantee that you are prepared for the unexpected, taking every precaution to eliminate your organization&#39;s cybercrime risk. Our comprehensive cyber security services incorporate critical safeguards such as anti-malware/ransomware, anti-phishing, anti-social engineering, and anti-data manipulation measures, as well as malware/ransomware detection techniques and&nbsp;cloud services based on security services and cloud services based on multifactor authentication.</span></span></p>\r\n', '<p><span style=\"font-size:22px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>The Advantages Of Hiring A Cybersecurity Service Provider</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Without the appropriate cyber security services in place, your organization and its employees remain vulnerable to cyber-attacks. Naturally, each organization&#39;s vulnerabilities are unique, but whether you want to ensure that your employees are &#39;cyber secure&#39; while working remotely, need to improve data protection, or require regular penetration testing to identify vulnerabilities, we can provide an effective cyber security solution. You may do the following with aammsecurities&nbsp;as your cyber security provider:</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Safeguard your reputation</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Secure your networks against unauthorized access</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Safeguard confidential information</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Comply with regulations and avoid potentially expensive violations</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Rapid resolution of problems</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Rapid response in the case of a breach</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Convince customers</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<p><span style=\"font-size:22px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Introducing Our Cyber Security Services</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">If you plan for the worst-case scenario, you will never be caught off guard. We begin by listening to your problems and developing an effective security plan to address new threats such as Malware, ransomware, phishing attacks, social engineering attacks, and data manipulation attacks. Ransomware/malware and phishing detection techniques &nbsp;along with cloud security&nbsp; services </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:22px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Solutions for Cyber Security</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Protect yourself against cyber attacks today, or learn more about our variety of IT support services. We regularly receive the following queries, and if you have similar concerns, call us now to discuss how to secure your business and infrastructure.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Is it necessary for me to use a password manager?</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">When Is the Appropriate Time to Change My Password?</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">We&#39;ve cracked the Phishing business now, correct? Our computers will now block harmful emails and prevent me from visiting hazardous websites, correct?</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Why should my UK-based business be concerned about hackers?</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">We live in a real-world, and occasionally Cyber Security safeguards fail or are circumvented by hackers; how can I defend my organization from this risk?</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">What Cyber Security Services do I require the most, and what will they protect me from?</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">What are the most recent techniques you&#39;ve observed attackers employ?</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">How can I determine which risks are important to my industry and, more precisely, my organization?</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">How can I keep abreast of Current and Emerging Threats to my Sector?</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">If I become aware of a specific Threat that is likely to harm my business, who can assist me in determining my potential exposure and the steps necessary to mitigate it?</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">How are other parties gaining access to my organization&#39;s data, and what are they doing with it?</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', '2021-09-14 07:25:56'),
(2, 'Cyber Incident Recovery', '<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">We are available 24 hours a day to assist organizations in recovering from cyber incidents. We collaborate with both internal IT teams and third-party IT suppliers to guarantee a coordinated, efficient, and recovery-oriented strategy.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">We are available to assist you wherever and whenever you require.</span></span></p>\r\n', '<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:22px\"><strong>Uncertain about what to do next?</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">You are not alone in this. We collaborate with top cyber insurance carriers and incident response organizations to assist them and their clients in the recovery process following a cyber incident. Rapid restoration of operating capacity is important to ensure that you are back up and running, securely, and able to carry on with your company.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:22px\"><strong>We prioritize you.</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Our objective is to swiftly restore your operating capabilities. We work alongside your internal teams to guarantee that your requirements are prioritized.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:22px\"><strong>We are here </strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">We are available 24 hours a day, 7 days a week, all year. We are here whenever you want assistance. Cybercriminals operate on a 24-hour basis, just like we do.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:22px\"><strong>We assist you in innovating.</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">We gain an understanding of your systems and how you operate as part of the recovery process. Armed with this knowledge, we will collaborate with you to ensure that your future condition is as favourable as possible.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:22px\"><strong>We safeguard your safety.</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">We will not only assist you in recovering. We will ensure that everything is done safely and securely. Not only for the now but also for the future</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:22px\"><strong>Our Approach</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Our approach to resolving cyber incidents is clear. Prevention, detection, forensic and recovery </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Prevention, detection, and forensic response form the four-part cybernetic defensive cycle. The four primary approaches to identify, cope, and deal with an issue are prevention, detection, reaction, and forensic.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">The prevention is continuously monitored in order to discover any potential vulnerability or malfunction.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">&nbsp;The detection segment includes network IDS (such as Network IDS), host-based IDS (such as Host base IDS), signature-based IDS (such as Signature-based IDS), and anomaly-based IDS (such as Anomaly-based IDS). Good or malicious traffic on our server is detectable using Wireshark, telling us about the attacker.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">This uses the response phase to get rid of the assault rapidly.</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">During an assault, when a system is healed and then healed again, the forensic phase is utilized</span></span></p>\r\n', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:24px; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:22px\"><strong>Our both technological and tactical approaches.</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">To safeguard the system, a physical system, referred to as the monitored system, is employed. The monitored system contains the system configuration, including the network topology and configuration</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">The number of sensors that convey all control system events to the processing environment.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Intrusion signals, software upgrades, and hardware installs are all elements of these kinds of events.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">These products include IDS, Antivirus (AV), and firmware.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Countermeasures like blocking TCP/UDP ports, diverting inbound traffic, or putting in a route may be implemented in order to mitigate possible acknowledgement of receipt issues.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Responding to vulnerability also includes measuring and monitoring the vulnerability response. Network topology is accurate.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Verifying technical data that has not been prepared and turned into remedial activities and generating a list of possible countermeasures will all be performed.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Attack models can&nbsp;be built using vulnerability tests being used as a starting point.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">The balance between the expense of the reaction and the machine&#39;s safety phase is in the Select action for countermeasures. Additionally, the presence of non-compliance becomes a concern when determining the monetary worth of activating the specified motions, as compliance reduction has the potential to decrease the provision of certain services potentially. Separate and evaluate various defence methods for a particular assault and see whether they may be the most useful, the most cost-effective, the most limit-compliant, or the most profitable.</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">It is equally vital to utilize modern and secure software to detect assault, not only to keep data safe. Wireshark may also be used for the identification of attacker exploits</span></span></p>\r\n', '2021-09-14 07:56:16'),
(3, 'Do\'s & Don\'ts', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Security is not as straightforward as it once was. At aammsecurities, we encounter cyber security risks on a daily basis. The dangers are increasing in number and sophistication, and the danger is quite real.&nbsp;The days of a virus writer developing infections for &quot;fun,&quot; political, or anti-establishment motives are long gone; nowadays, it is a major business, whether consumers pay to decrypt their data or send money to a fraudster &ndash; which happens every day.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">While technology and software can help mitigate risk, the risk can never be completely eliminated, owing mostly to human behaviour and social engineering. This is how the vast majority of large-scale scams are perpetrated. Criminals initiate frauds, but the victim frequently assists them. Consider what someone is requesting of you. If you are requested to click a link, open a file, pay money, or verify information, STOP AND CONSIDER.</span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">We provide prevention techniques and countermeasures against malware/ransomware attacks, phishing attacks, social engineering and data manipulation attacks .</span></span></p>\r\n', '<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:22px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\"><a name=\"_Toc80752979\"></a><a name=\"_Toc81416204\">Countermeasures to Malware Attacks</a></span></span></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif\">Training of the users minimizes the danger of infection. The typical route for a ransomware attack begins with a fraudulent email. Once users have been taught, they will recognize and avoid some of their attack methods. Social engineering is an assault that focuses on more privileged users on the network. It is assumed that these individuals have essential company or personal data stored locally or have access to crucial systems and infrastructure. The likelihood that the firm will pay the ransom grows as a result. Installing the latest patch is especially important for firmware, anti-malware programs, operating systems, and third-party software. New ransomware versions are created constantly, and most anti-malware programs include anti-worm/anti-virus capabilities that identify newer ransomware variants. Restoring data from a backup is the best approach to recover against ransomware. If backups restore data from an alternate source, then it bypasses the ransom demand. A hacker would do this because backup files are standard. Thus, a ransomware virus monitors the network for these files. Even when a backup has been restored, the network must be decontaminated of the ransomware. Keeping a separate backup copy offshore prevents Malware from encrypting backup files. For companies, remote cloud backups are typically the preferred backup method. Storing information in the cloud lets users be protected from ransomware and other security risks, including viruses. Typically, malware attacks originate via executables or scripts that are used to download and execute the program. Ransomware attacks are not always immediate. Ransomware such as CryptoLocker might lie dormant until a specific date. A wide range of programs is used to identify ransomware on a network. Malware creates a massive number of files whose names have been changed. There are dozens of different forms of ransomware viruses that may be detected by anti-malware software. The signatures in the encrypted file detect ransomware before it is allowed to run. Zero-day attacks that target vulnerabilities developers have not yet discovered they are not always seen&mdash;current anti-malware solutions, including artificial intelligence (ai), machine learning, and behaviour monitoring. The results of these tests measure the current file state against the addition and deletion of files and access requests. They notify administrators of possible attack activity in order to avert data encryption and destruction of files. As an effective way to combat ransomware, utilize anti-malware software, frequent file backups, and user training. Even while no cyber defences can guarantee total protection, users can drastically minimize the likelihood of a successful assault</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<h2 style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:22px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><a name=\"_Toc80752989\"></a><a name=\"_Toc81416215\">Countermeasures to </a>Social Engineering </span></span></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif\">Social engineering attacks make use of human interaction. Therefore countermeasures should focus on raising knowledge of such assaults</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\"><a name=\"_Toc80753000\"></a></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:22px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\"><a name=\"_Toc81416226\">Countermeasure to Phishing Attacks</a></span></span></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif\">When consumers have several unread messages, they should never assume that they have not yet viewed the email because of their stress or other competing messages. They have till now to go over the email and assess it. Let the screen capture fly over the URL and hover over it. Check to see if anything looks wrong and report it if so. Check the email&#39;s &quot;return-path&quot; and &quot;reply-to&quot; fields to determine where users got their email. Even if they do not use email, they should sandbox to be safe. Fraudulent emails will not be clicked if customers do not trust the emails their bank sends and do not allow any attachments except personal salutations, such as &#39;Dear [first name],&#39; to download. They also do not allow attachment downloads that might lead to further issues. Automatic transaction numbers are issued when users issue a request for transaction details in online banking. Also, since phishing attempts have no chance, they are pointless.<a name=\"_Toc80753002\"></a><a name=\"_Toc81416228\"></a></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:22px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Countermeasures to Data-Manipulation</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif\">Using an encrypted method to convey sensitive and essential data is one way to use encryption. If the user would like, it may also use Pretty Good Privacy (PGP) or an equivalent like GPG. While WinZip and 7-zip are good archiving tools, encryption using AES-256 with a pre-shared key that is only delivered in an encrypted email message does the trick. Authentication, Both sides of a communication stream or transaction should use digital certificates to authenticate each other. Letting that happen allows users to guarantee that both the person to whom sending it and the person receiving it from are whom they say they are and that the channel is encrypted. In addition, it is beneficial for the distribution of data via automatic means. For example, financial transactions must occur between two software applications operating in different places. The information must be protected so that it does not get into the wrong hands. It is crucial and critical information that cannot be trusted to be sent only via routes that cannot be hacked. To ensure that a request is genuine, that the requestor is permitted to receive it, and that the sender is authorized to submit it, a user must contact the requestor personally. Procedural documentation should include several checks in order to decrease the risk.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"page-break-after:always\"><span style=\"display:none\">&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '2021-09-14 07:31:22');

