(1, 'Aammsecurities | Home', 'Aammsecurities', 'Revolutionize the way you secure the data, resources, and users in your network with aammsecurities', 'cd4be3cde8c79f45cd5d67b785e4496b.jpg', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">The rapid digital transformation of the banking industry has increased the potential attack surface, exposing firms to cyber threats. As more organizations utilize digital banking, having robust cybersecurity policies is critical. Understanding which threat trends provide the most significant risk to your bank or financial institution is critical to the success of these programs informed security tactics that appropriately analyze the organization&#39;s cyberhealth. Enabling the bank to embrace digital transformation without compromising security or compliance is possible with security monitoring software.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:16.5pt\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">The banking industry&#39;s cyber threat landscape</span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Cybercriminals are increasingly targeting consumer banking credentials while carrying out attacks due to the increased value of financial data. Mobile banking applications used by more banks on the network create new weaknesses for hackers to exploit. Both client-side and server-side attacks may be employed against banking apps, making them especially challenging to defend. The same rules that apply to devices apply to servers as well. Bank customers should be wary of fraudsters who will also seek to attack the bank&#39;s third-party providers (software vendors, banking equipment vendors, customer service vendors). Threat actors typically target vendors because they have access to sensitive banking data, which may often be found on the vendor&#39;s systems. Monitoring the cybersecurity of banks that depend on third parties is critical. The proper level of due diligence applied to vendors may safeguard financial companies from damage to their reputation and significant financial loss.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:15.0pt\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Three significant threats that banks should be aware of are as follows.&nbsp;</span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:16.5pt\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Malware</span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Malware has for a long time threatened the financial sector. Malware is being used to infect weak user devices, allowing thieves to access a complete banking network and steal valuable user data. More recently, malware has been easier to get, and it has thus risen in prominence since it was the Cause of more than 75% of all data breaches in the banking industry in 2019. Due to the rapid expansion of malware-as-a-service and file-less malware assaults, it is apparent that banks and financial institutions require robust security measures. A crucial step in ensuring that the devices of both customers and employees cannot be compromised is for banks to cooperate with their security teams to configure security systems to prevent both customers and employees from being infected by malware.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:16.5pt\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Phishing</span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Social engineering attacks are a unique type of hacking since they use human behavior to access corporate computers. Employees&#39; passwords and other critical information are stolen by social engineers who exploit the information to infiltrate the network. Banking is a popular target for social engineering attacks, namely phishing. Fake emails, phone calls, and messages sent by imposters attempt to mislead corporate personnel into revealing confidential information. Not only may phishing assaults utilize incorrect URLs to trick employees into downloading malware on their systems, but this method can also be used to install malware. In phishing attempts, customers are commonly targeted. Thus it must educate customers about cybersecurity best practices. A security awareness newsletter or email can be used to disseminate this information.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:16.5pt\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Data Manipulation</span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Many people believe that just data theft is what worries them about cyber assaults. While data manipulation assaults have become a standard attack for hackers, that is not always the case. Attackers that successfully infiltrate a target system make undetectable alterations to data on their behalf for personal benefit. For example, if an employee updates customer transactional data, it illustrates this principle in operation. The transactions will likely go unreported since people will perceive them as legitimate, resulting in subsequent data entries being incorrect. As the manipulation continues to go unnoticed, it will inflict more significant harm. These attacks are difficult to detect and avoid because altered data look no different than standard data. In the financial business, deliberate data manipulation can lead to severe fines and non-compliance with data standards.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:16.5pt\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Find out how to ensure banking institution is safe from cyber-attacks.</span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:16.5pt\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Multi-factor Authentication</span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Multi-factor authentication requires the user to provide two or more different forms of authentication yet only grants access once. Passwords, pins, and fingerprints are all accepted as logins. To protect the security of MFA, avoid logging in with the same credentials (i.e., two passwords) as this weakens it. Additionally, MFA offers another degree of protection while accessing valuable information to protect customers&#39; information.</span><br />\r\n&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:16.5pt\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Cyber risk assessment</span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">To do a cyber risk assessment, businesses should survey their network&#39;s vulnerabilities. To identify the main threats to the organization, evaluate the company&#39;s vulnerability, prioritize repair activities, and streamline threat mitigation. This ensures that can proactively guard against data breaches while saving expenses and reducing worker hours. Regulations and industry standards necessitate &quot;continuous monitoring&quot; as a result of mounting risks to data. Organizations are reminded of possible dangers by the presence of articles and blog postings, which call attention to weaknesses. Many individuals, however, view security vulnerabilities as theoretical rather than concrete tasks. All of the organization is IT, and business executives must speak the same language regarding information.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nSecurity and have mutual knowledge of what it means to do vulnerability management to work together to safeguard sensitive data.</span><br />\r\n&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:16.5pt\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Cyber insurance</span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Cyber insurance is a must for a cybersecurity plan since it helps guarantee that organizations are financially covered in a data breach. Not only does cyber insurance warn consumers of data breaches, but it also informs them of regulatory requirements, which companies must comply with to stay by data privacy rules. Also, cyber insurance will cover the cost of repairing damaged systems and restore. To safeguard enterprises against data breaches, companies rely on cyber insurance. Cyber insurance plans remain naturally hesitant to be issued since understanding the client&#39;s cyber health might be challenging. Better risk management and constant monitoring of customers are two results that accurate security ratings may produce for carriers, reinsurers, brokers, and risk managers. Because such valuable data is involved, the financial services sector has been a frequent target for hackers. Financial institutions that store personal financial information (PII) on their systems is vulnerable to a compromise without the proper cybersecurity safeguards. Banks and other financial institutions are at risk of substantial penalties and loss of reputation in the case of a breach. Therefore compliance is a significant issue. Therefore, in the financial services business, compliance with cybersecurity standards is critical. An efficient cybersecurity compliance program would help banks comply with laws put in place by different government organizations while safeguarding critical assets. This means that companies will avoid penalties by ensuring compliance with established banking standards.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:16.5pt\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Employee training</span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Companies must train the workers on cyber hygiene best practices for all information security measures to be effective. Employee training can also help to reduce the consequences of a data leak. Train staff to utilize their cybersecurity systems effectively, and they may detect and help patch flaws before they can be exploited. For many years, hackers have targeted financial institutions because of the wealth of valuable information housed on their networks. However, the digital revolution in the business has seen a rise in assaults. As banks integrate digital solutions, the number of places at which hackers may launch an assault increases. Many financial institutions can no longer safeguard essential data such as credit card information, banking statements, and client social security numbers because legacy systems are no longer equipped to resist today&#39;s sophisticated cyber-attacks. Financial institutions must put cyber hygiene at the top of their priority list to facilitate a secure digital transition. Companies will be better equipped to find and fix vulnerabilities in their internal and third-party ecosystems by using cybersecurity strategies. To fulfill the client&#39;s demand for innovation, businesses will maintain secure and compliant operations while offering new financial products. If the organization uses third-party suppliers to execute commercial operations, it must keep an eye on the cybersecurity of those third-party vendors. An organization&#39;s approach to cybersecurity may be evaluated using questionnaires that gather the information needed. It is, however, labor-intensive to create surveys that are vendor-specific.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">To make matters worse, most companies establish security policies to promote software development. Guidelines established to mitigate cybersecurity risk serve as a reference for suppliers. Using these standards, assessing third-party vendor risk gives a more realistic picture of each company&#39;s risk, helping to cut down on questionnaire management time.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">&emsp;<br />\r\n<strong><span style=\"font-size:16.5pt\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">How can aammsecurities help?</span></span></strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Banks need visibility into their cybersecurity ecosystems in order to effectively protect themselves against threats. Countermeasures and cyberattack detection techniques are provided by aammsecurities so that cyber hazards can be quickly identified and threat remediation can be prioritized. Cloud Services based on security services and Cloud Services based on multi-factor authentication are also available from aammsecurities. so that they can readily defend banks against cyber-attacks</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Cybercriminals seeking to hack systems for financial gain will always target the banking sector. You can improve your security capabilities and ensure that vital assets are safeguarded using aammsecurities </span></span></p>\r\n', NULL, NULL, 'home', 1, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL),
(2, 'Managed IT Services', 'Managed IT Services', NULL, '81057ecb67c214f897b1955a669b97e5.jpg', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:22px\">Your Information Technology Infrastructure Deserves Reliable and Stable IT Support</span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">At aammsecurities, we believe in developing long-term relationships with our clients. Because each organization is unique, there is no one-size-fits-all approach to managing information technology and ensuring that infrastructure is safe, secure, and operational. We invest time and attention in learning about your organization, determining how your IT is presently working and identifying areas for improvement.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Whether you&#39;re having significant IT challenges, don&#39;t feel confident about your data security, or need assistance transferring key workloads to the cloud, we can help you sort it all out and make educated business decisions - preparing you for the needs of tomorrow&#39;s world.</span></span></p>\r\n', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:22px\"><strong>Remote IT Support Available 24 hours a day, 7 days a week, and on any schedule</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\">We take the time to learn about you, your employees, and the way your organization operates so that regardless of whether you require full or partial remote assistance, you will always interact with an expert who is thoroughly familiar with your IT architecture, network, and systems.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p st